summaries.short: The detectives draw parallels from tragedies in Christopher’s past to better understand his willingness to sacrifice everything for Susan.
summaries.full: As they narrow in on the likeliest scenarios from that tragic night, Lancing and Wilkie’s focus shifts to Christopher’s past. While they exploit his recurring tendency to go too far for those he loves, the couple’s relationship with Susan’s parents comes under the spotlight. Then, Lancing and Wilkie have a breakthrough that calls the couple’s shared reality into question.

summaries.short: As their trial begins, Susan and Christopher grapple with their greatest threat yet: the very real possibility of being separated forever.
summaries.full: With their trial underway, Susan and Christopher each take the stand for a final chance to prove their version of that fatal night in the Wycherley home. Truth and fantasy clash as old doubts and new regrets test the limits of their love, before the couple faces their greatest threat yet: the imminent possibility of being separated forever.

summaries.short: As the detectives work to pick apart Susan and Christopher’s united front, a painful secret from the past comes back to haunt the couple.
summaries.full: Shortly after turning themselves over to the Nottinghamshire Police, Susan and Christopher are thrown into separate holding cells, where their statements are picked apart by detectives Emma Lancing and Paul Wilkie. As the past comes back to haunt her, concerning details from Chris’ interview make their way to Susan, and a painful secret is revealed.

summaries.short: The building blocks of Christopher and Susan Edwards’ carefully reconstructed life begin to collapse after a single phone call.
summaries.full: After living in France with his wife Susan for the last 15 years, Christopher Edwards places a desperate call to his stepmother back in England for financial help. But when Tabitha relays the details of their conversation to the police, a resulting double homicide investigation quickly builds steam, and the couple’s carefully reconstructed lives are suddenly placed at risk.
